	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Kiting is bad!</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I'm not sure if any other classes get anything comparable, but with a shadow specced priest with mind flay, they can basically kite mobs.  It's a 50% snare with dot damage.  Priests can solo kite kill elite mobs higher level than them with the judicious use of this spell.  They should either remove the snare effect, or increase/add a cooldown to this spell.  <br />
<br />
Also note it's instant cast and low mana cost if you use the mind flay 1 spell just for the snare effect.<br />
<br />
I just don't want any classes to be bogged down into the "have to kite" mode as thier soloing option.  Kiting imho is just lame and should never be encouraged.<br />
<br />
Thoughts? Opinions? Flames?<br />
<br />
Xerkos</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
