	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>how is kiting bad?<br />
<br />
it takes more skill than just standing there and hitting a certain sequence of spell buttons. you have to deal with turning to run and cast, deal with watching out for additional agro while running around, and make sure you stay within the immediate area so the mob doesnt evade to its spawn point, which greatly restricts your kiting paths.<br />
<br />
staying out of the mobs melee range is the best way to survive for a non-defensive class. however, i do agree that kiting should be time restricted by manapool, and it should not be possible to continuously extend the kite just off of spirit regen (in other words, the mana usage to keep the kite going should be > a characters spirit regen). also, for a class that has a large number of defense capabilities to counter melee damage, it does seem kind of pointless to give priests such a strong snare, at least at so cheap a mana cost. starting the snare effect low and increasing it up to 50% over the levels, so the higher cost snare is required for effective snaring, should work well enough.<br />
<br />
imo, kiting is good, as long as it is limited by mana, and as long as there is an easier way to kill normal mobs.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
