		<div>Frog, i think the point is that no classes should be forced to resort to Kiting tricks to solo.  Remember that kiting was invented because of Verants insanely stupid stance against soloing.  So people used Verants rules against them and did it anyway.  Thus the invention of Kiting.<br />
<br />
In WoW Kiting isnt, and shouldnt, be nessecary because each class has means to solo.  People will find ways to do it anyway but the important thing here is not to put artificial, immersion breaking, and stupid gameplay restrictions in place to "kill it dead" but to make it overall less efficient and more boring so very few people will do it.  I dont mind the fact that a shadow priest can solo stuff by kiting....its gonna take so long and be so boring that in the end it isnt worth it unless you are fighting some really tough mobs and cant find a group to help you.  Most of the time these players will be doing what they are supposed to be doing and not kiting.</div>
